      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I am so sorry you are carrying this heavy burden of loss. Ten years is a long time to navigate a world that feels empty, and the way your identity shifts when you wake up is a profound sign of how deeply they were woven into your life. Please know that your pain is valid, and you don't have to \"do this\" alone.\n\nWhile I can't erase the past or force you to feel whole again, I can offer a different perspective on how to move forward, even if it feels impossible right now. Sometimes, the very act of acknowledging the grief is the first step toward rebuilding a sense of self, even if that self is different from who you were before.\n\nIf you are feeling like you can't take another morning, please consider reaching out to a trusted friend, a support group, or a mental health professional who can walk beside you through these difficult days. You are not alone in this struggle, and there are people ready to listen and help you find your way forward.",
